<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Chargé in Bolivia (
                        Adam
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d282</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">282</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-06-15T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/6–1546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Adam</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-15T18:00:00-04:00">June 15, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>331. Representatives <gloss target="#t_AP1">AP</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_UP1">UP</gloss> and Grace have asked us express to you their appreciation your
                    assistance (second paragraph <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 535 and
                        <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 533).</p>
                <p>For your confidential information we have recommended to Grace their company
                    immediately dispatch responsible official American citizen to La Paz to take
                    temporary charge and to investigate charges political activity by Grace Bolivian
                    personnel. In latter connection Grace informed that while in absence proof we
                    assumed no political activity their personnel we would view any such activity
                    with extreme disfavor (see Dept press release of December 11, 1945 regarding
                    attitude participation American companies in local political affairs).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
